# Backend Rules

## Stack
- FastAPI (main.py, routers/)
- psycopg3 for Lakebase Postgres (NOT psycopg2)
- OAuth token rotation per connection — see db.py
- Databricks Apps deployment with Database resource

## Database connection pattern
- Always use `get_conn()` from db.py — never create connections directly
- Tokens expire — each request gets a fresh connection
- Use parameterized queries: `execute("SELECT ... WHERE id = %s", (id,))`
- Never use f-strings or string formatting in SQL

## ETL (etl/clean.py)
- HLES Excel columns have leading `\n` characters
- Normalization: `re.sub(r'\s+', '_', col.strip().lower())`
- See docs/HANDOFF-ETL-PHASE2.md for correct column mappings
- Customer name = ADJ FNAME + ADJ LNAME concatenated
- BM name comes from org_mapping lookup, not HLES data

## Deployment
- `npm run build` before deploying (frontend must be rebuilt)
- Push via git to trigger Databricks Apps redeploy
- Never push secrets or .env files
